ashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]},{"name":"Anna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[{"name":"Anne","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]},{"name":"Maria","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Maria  , of German origin but now also moderately popular in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Elizabeth Anna Maria de Bedmore was born in 1340, in Stamford, Lincolnshire, England. She married Sir Thomas Hunt in 1359, in Gosfield, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died after 1354, in Hertford, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1340–Aft 1354":"1340–pärast 1354","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1355–1437":"1355–1437","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1340–1354":"1340–1354","1437":"1437","1355":"1355","Aft 1354":"pärast 1354","1354":"1354","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, England","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hertford, Hertfordshire, England":"Hertford, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1340–Aft 1354":"1340–1354 jälkeen","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1355–1437":"1355–1437","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1340–1354":"1340–1354","1437":"1437","1355":"1355","Aft 1354":"1354 jälkeen","1354":"1354","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, England","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hertford, Hertfordshire, England":"Hertford, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1340–Aft 1354":"1340–après 1354","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1355–1437":"1355–1437","1355–Male":"1355–Décédé","1340–1354":"1340–1354","1437":"1437","1355":"1355","Aft 1354":"après 1354","1354":"1354","1340":"1340","1407":"1407","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hertford, Hertfordshire, England":"Hertford, Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Elizabeth Anna Maria de Bedmore est née en 1340, à Stamford, Lincolnshire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Sir Thomas Hunt en 1359, à Gosfield, Essex, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils. Elle est décédée après 1354, à Hertford, Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1340–Aft 1354":"1340–nach 1354","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1355–1437":"1355–1437","1355–Male":"1355–Verstorben","1340–1354":"1340–1354","1437":"1437","1355":"1355","Aft 1354":"nach 1354","1354":"1354","1340